This paper deals with improving the accuracy of Automated Fingerprint Identification Systems (AFIS) using extended minutia types. The paper involves image processing and pattern recognition techniques, which are commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with forensic science and criminal investigations, which are related to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper uses a database of fingerprints, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Finally, the paper involves experiments and evaluations, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM).
